msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/sphinxcontrib_rust/nodes.py:docstring
#: of sphinxcontrib_rust.nodes.Node:3
msgid ""
"The node is a dataclass that encapsulates the details of a Rust token and "
"how to format it in the signature. The type of the node indicates which "
"docutils element type is used for docutils node of the output. The value is "
"the text to display in the node. It is required for all node types except "
"``SPACE``, ``NEWLINE`` and ``RETURNS``. The ``target`` is only used for "
"``LINK`` nodes to generate a link to the target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/sphinxcontrib_rust/nodes.py:docstring
#: of sphinxcontrib_rust.nodes.Node.create_signature:1
msgid ""
"Create a Rust item signature under the ``signode`` from the given ``nodes``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/sphinxcontrib_rust/nodes.py:docstring
#: of sphinxcontrib_rust.nodes.Node.create_signature:3
msgid ""
"The method will also add the generated nodes as children of the given "
"``signode`` properly accounting for any multiline signatures. In case of "
"multiline signatures, the permalink is added to the first line."
msgstr ""

